Like the moon, there are places on this earth that seem distant and beyond reach. With the knowledge of what has come before, of what has been achieved by those wearing an @OMEGA speedmaster, I am pushed to explore the unknown. To seek the highest mountains, roam unfamiliar landscapes, to travel to the remote reaches of this planet. #Moonwatch #OMEGAmychoice

As the @OMEGA Speedmaster turns 60 this year, it remains one of the only watches qualified by NASA for spaceflight, and still the only one qualified for use outside the spacecraft. Tested to extreme conditions, it is designed to be worn on the surface of the moon, but fares equally well on a day to day.  #Moonwatch #OMEGAmychoice

This watch defines a time when everything became possible. The @OMEGA Speedmaster was the first watch on the moon, worn by the astronauts as part of NASAâ€™s famed Apollo 11 mission. Holding this watch, Iâ€™m briefly transported to a time when science and human exploration was pushed to its limits.  A time defined by a single step onto the surface of something unknown, a moment when the seemingly impossible and unachievable, became reality. #Moonwatch #omegamychoice

Things I learned from our 'Green Kitchen At Home' cooking class at @surlatable in New York today. 
1. I talk way too much.

3. This pilaf salad took a lot longer for our attendees to prepare than we thought it would.

Kami baru saja selesai Umrah, dengan prosesi dari jam 11 malam waktu Mekkah sampai jam 3:30 pagi ini tadi.

Setelah tahalul (memotong sedikit rambut) di Masjidil Haram, rekan Mutawif mengantarkan saya untuk cukur habis sesuai dengan yang dilaksanakan oleh Rasulullah.

Seperti yang bisa Anda lihat pada foto, untuk beberapa saat saya tidak mungkin bisa kibas rambut.

Selama proses Tawaf (mengelilingi Ka'bah sebanyak 7 kali) dan Sai, kami menaikkan banyak doa dan harapan bagi kebaikan kami, keluarga, dan Anda semua yang sudah menitipkan doa kepada kami.

Semoga dalam waktu yang tidak lama kita semua mulai melihat perbaikan dan perkembangan seperti yang menjadi doa dan harapan kita selama ini.

Aamiin

Alhamdulillah, kami sudah sampai di Mekkah setelah 7 jam perjalanan darat dari Madinah.

Sebentar lagi kami makan malam dan bersiap-siap untuk Tawaf dan Sai di Masjidil Haram.

Semoga Anda yang merindukan undangan Allah untuk hadir di Tanah Suci, ikhlas mengajukan diri untuk diundang.

Niatkanlah dan upayakanlah.

Anda harus yang memulai, setelah itu Tuhan yang akan memastikan Anda sampai di Baitullah dengan selamat dan sejahtera.

Dalam Tawaf dan Sai nanti kami akan aminkan semua doa yang sudah Anda titipkan kepada kami.

Semoga kehidupan ini indah, sejahtera, dan membahagiakan bagi kita semua.

Foto tahun 2005 bersama anak-anak di Singapura.

Marco masih 5 tahun, dan Audrey 9 tahun. Pada tahun itu juga mereka Umrah.

Doa saya selalu untuk Ibu Linna adalah agar dia selalu sehat dan panjang umur, karena kami semua sangat bergantung kepadanya.

Semua urusan saya dan anak-anak menjadi tugas Ibu Linna, dan harus tuntas semuanya dengan baik sebelum dia sempat mengurusi dirinya sendiri.

Maka sebetulnya kalau orang melihat saya dan anak-anak sehat, ceria, dan berhasil dalam pekerjaan dan studi - itu karena Ibu Linna.

Itu sebabnya wanita yang baik bukan hanya menjadikan kita laki-laki yang baik, tapi juga menjadikan keluarga kita tertata dan tenteram. 
Wanita yang baik bukan hanya menjadi perhiasan terindah bagi suaminya, tapi menjadikan rumah tangganya sebagai Surga di dunia.

Dan saat badai fitnah menerjang, istri yang baik menjadi tameng, benteng, centeng, dan pengenteng beban hati.

Semoga Anda yang masih sendiri disandingkan dengan dia yang mengindahkan hati dan kehidupan Anda, dalam keluarga yang sehat, ceria, sejahtera, dan bahagia.

Dan semoga kita semua selalu berada dalam perawatan penuh cinta dari Tuhan Yang Maha Pemurah.

Aamiin

Salam sayang dari Ibu Linna dan Oppa Haji di Madinah ðŸ’ŸðŸ’ðŸ’–

Bersama berlian hati saya di depan salah satu pintu Masjid Nabawi yang indah itu.

Semakin kita menua semakin kita akan menyadari bahwa Tuhan mengutamakan orang yang mengutamakan Tuhan.

Mohon maaf jika saya memberikan contoh seperti berikut ini:

Seorang rekan hidupnya sibuk kejar mengejar antara biaya dan pendapatan, dan mengeluh tentang kapan hidup ini memapan.

Saya anjurkan dia untuk Umrah, karena dia sudah lebih dari mampu untuk itu.

Dia menjawab singkat, bahwa dia mau upgrade mobilnya dari merk Jepang ke merk Jerman dulu.

Saya sampaikan bahwa dengan lebih mengutamakan Tuhan, kita akan lebih disejahterakan.

Tapi dia lebih ingin mobil baru daripada rindu Baitullah.

Hemm ... tapi memang setiap orang bebas memilih, hanya saja tidak ada orang yang bebas dari dampak dari pilihannya.

Marilah kita memperhatikan naik turunnya kualitas hidup ini, dan menghubungkannya dengan kualitas kedekatan kita dengan Tuhan.

Mudah-mudahan dengannya kita melihat bahwa kehidupan yang indah selalu:

Dengan nama Tuhan, karena Tuhan, dan untuk Tuhan.

Semoga doa-doa Anda segera dikabulkan oleh Tuhan Yang Maha Kaya, Maha Berkuasa, Maha Melindungi, dan Maha Pemurah.

Aamiin

Kami sudah bersama selama 22 tahun dan tidak sehari pun kami terpisah.

Memang tidak semua pasangan bisa selalu bersama seperti kami karena sifat dari pekerjaan dan pola hidup yang tidak memungkinkan, tapi kami membentuk dan mengatur pekerjaan dan pola hidup kami KARENA kami tidak ingin terpisah walau sehari.

Maka jadilah karir MT dan pola hidup keluarga MT.

Kami tidak mengizinkan pekerjaan dan uang menjadi lebih kuat daripada kebahagiaan kami.

Kerinduan kami untuk hidup dengan damai dan bahagia menentukan jenis pekerjaan dan pendapatan yang kami pilih, bukan sebaliknya.

Itu sebuah ketetapan yang tidak mudah, tapi kami sudah hidup damai dan bahagia bersama Audrey dan Marco dalam pilihan pola hidup ini, dan bersyukur telah diizinkan untuk bekerja dan berkarir dalam bidang yang melayani bagi kebahagiaan sesama.

Sudah tentu kebahagiaan kami menumbuhkan rasa iri dan ketidak-sukaan pada jiwa-jiwa yang tidak ikhlas diingatkan oleh Tuhan dengan kehidupan mereka yang belum damai.

Tapi, kami lebih berfokus pada kebaikan yang bisa kami bangun untuk keluarga dan yang bisa kami lebihkan untuk sesama, bukan untuk menurunkan kelas kehidupan dengan merasa geram tentang perilaku buruk orang-orang yang mendurhakai kehidupannya sendiri.

Hidup ini untuk berbahagia.

Dan bagaimana mungkin kita mencapai kebahagiaan jika sikap dan cara-cara kita tidak membahagiakan?

Semoga Tuhan mencerahkan pandangan hidup Anda, menyehatkan tubuh dan mendamaikan hati Anda, dalam keluarga yang berezeki besar dan dalam umur yang panjang.

You gotta reach out and grab whatever it is you're looking for in this life. Endless travel seems to be my calling at the moment, I know that it will one day change and the pace will naturally decline. There's so much cultural fear of difficulty and change in our lives and it's something I've learned to tackle head on as an individual. I only really ever feel alive now, when I challenge my comfort zones. I think there's a universal lesson in there somewhere, nothing deeply satisfying is obtained easily.

Well, Oreos are easily obtained but still, most stuff is hard.

The best things in life often come after the longest wait... This speaks for so many things in my life. Pursuing my dreams, all with adventures and my work continue to grow my patience every day. Like the Grand Canyon having been on my bucket list since I was little, also finally getting my puppy @timber_tails ðŸ¶, who has brought nothing but joy to my life. The timing was finally right. I have wanted a dog for ever and if I had got one sooner I wouldn't have him! I'll also be headed back to school in the fall for my teaching degree and this decision rose due to all the situations and adventures that had occurred in my life thus far... life is crazy but I wouldn't change a single thing about it. Athens is a real paradise for lovers of sea trips, renting a yacht here is as easy as renting a car. The city has largest ports for private yachts with comfortable berths capable of taking yachts of any level. For those who love unusual accommodation options the capital of Greece offer lots of botels (boats converted into hotels). For the past several years they have been in high demand among those who love romantic and interesting type of vacation!

During our test we'd stopped in small towns near Frankfurt for shooting. In each of them, in just a few minutes after the stop, the crowd of local residents appeared around our red Insignia Grand Sport asking a lot of questions about this eye-catching beauty from RÃ¼sselsheim. So to us it was always quite a task to shoot the car with no people around, even at night. The interest in new Insignia is huge, especially in this area of Germany, where Opel is not just a manufacturer, with whom the destinies of many generations of people are tied, but also the part of history and culture.

During our conversation in 2016 Mark Adams, Vice President of @opel Design in Europe, said to me that concept of Monza, presented in 2013, will have a big impact on the following models of this famous German car manufacturer. Indeed, the high-precision design of the new Insignia, which we've tested recently in Frankfurt, is surely the best confirmation of core design philosophy called 'Sculptural artistry meets German and technical precision'. The silhouette of the car is very elegant and it has a high aerodynamic properties!

Once they bloom, the massive crop of tulips just outside of Amsterdam have a short window to be enjoyed before workers cut them for vendors. 
Last year, I captured the crops just before the flowers were cut for a Day to Night image. This is a small portion of that image, which shows the almost unfathomable volume of beautiful tulips that are grown each year.

Last year, I had the honor of giving a TED talk on my series, Day to Night. This year, my Day to Night image of Easter Mass, 2016 at the Vatican was used to introduce  Pope Francis for his TED talk.

Day To Night, Grand Canyon National Park. 
While other images from my Day to Night series have proven to be quite challenging, this image was made even more complicated by sheer logistics. How would I create an image that showed one of the most photographed places in the world in a completely unique way? My goal was to create an image that showed the majesty and vastness of the Grand Canyon, incorporating a human scale and narrative within the scene. I photographed from the top of the Desert View Watchtower at the South Rim - in the late summer so that I could capture the summer storms - where my team and I worked for 27 hours scanning this amazing vista for all the unique moments from Day to Night. The long hours paid off and I was able to capture a single bolt of lightning just before the storm retreated into the canyon.

Day to Night, Tunnel View, Yosemite National Park. A portion of this image was featured on the cover of last year's January issue of National Geographic Magazine in honor of the 100th anniversary of the National Park Service. I am proud to celebrate our National Parks again for #nationalparksweek. 
Iâ€™ve always been inspired by the concept of using photography as a medium for capturing the passage of time. Time is something that we constantly sense, but have no concrete way of visualizing. Interestingly enough, this view, called "Tunnel View"  has remained truly timeless over the years.

In creating a Day To Night,  I photograph from locations and views that are part of our collective memory. Working from a fixed camera angle, I capture the fleeting moments of humanity and light as time passes. After photographing for up to 26 hours and over 1500 images taken, I select the best moments of the day and night. Using time as my guide, all these moments are then seamlessly blended into a single photograph, visualizing our conscious journey with time.

It is my hope that this image captures the magical experience that is Yosemite seen by millions, in the 100 operating years of the National Park Service.

Stay tuned to see more of our National Parks, including the completed images from my current series, Day to Night. 
#Yosemite #StephenWilkes #NationalParks #Family #GoOutside

Day to Night, Vatican City on Easter Sunday. 
Over 150,000 people were in attendance last Easter when Pope Francis held Easter Mass from Vatican City. 
It was an impressive and beautiful day for Catholics and non-Catholics alike - the historical importance alone made it one of my most important captures yet. As one of the most beloved Popes it was a great honor to create this photograph and include him.

Did you know the Smithsonian helped save the American bison from extinction? In this @smithsonianarchives photo, a group of kids look at the first bison at the National Zoo in 1899. #tbt 
When William Hornaday (later the first director of @smithsonianzoo) traveled to Montana in 1886 to collect specimens for an exhibition at the National Museum, he was surprised at how decimated the bison herds had become due to hunting. 
To educate the public about the importance of their conservation, he created an exhibition about them in the museum and even put live bison on display behind the Castleâ€”a precursor to the Zoo in our own backyard. 
Learn about more conservation success stories this Friday through Sunday by following #EarthOptimism.

Weâ€™re celebrating the centennial of her birth and the legendary career that followed with this portrait on view at our @smithsoniannpg. 
It shows Fitzgerald performing, flanked by Ray Brown (left), Dizzy Gillespie (right) and Milt Jackson (far right). The photographer, William P. Gottlieb, learned to use a camera so that he could include images in his weekly music column for The Washington Post. 
Today, his photos of jazz musicians from the 1930s and â€™40s are regarded as invaluable visual records of jazzâ€™s Golden Age.

Did you know orchids make up 10 percent of the worldâ€™s plant species? But more than half of native orchids in North America are listed as threatened or endangered in some part of their home range. 
Researchers at @smithsonianenvironment are working to save the 200-plus species like this one, Galearis spectabilis, which is common in Maryland. 
Theyâ€™re studying the interactions between orchids and fungiâ€”a complex, symbiotic relationship in which each of the orchidsâ€™ life stages depend to some extent on specific fungi.

Happy #Easter! This early 20th-century postcard is one of more than 3,000 real photo postcards in our @amhistorymuseumâ€‹'s Photographic History Collection.

Real photo postcards, made on thick photo paper with the postcard info pre-printed on the back, were popular from around 1900 to World War I.

In 1907, postal regulations changed to allow senders to put messages AND addresses on the backâ€”before, only addresses went there. This kept the front free from writing and the image unmarked.

Once thought to be extinct, black-footed ferrets are rebounding through Smithsonian science.

Railay beach in Thailand is just one of those places that you want to return to again and again.

Aerial image of snorkel boats at Sombrero Key coral reef in the Florida Keys. The dark spots in the turquoise water are coral heads made up of millions of tiny animals called polyps. Violent tornado crossing the prairies of South Dakota. I've been asked many times if I have photos or video of flying cows? The answer is no, but almost. The little black dots in the green field are cows in South Dakota with a violent Tornado heading straight for them. There is a famous quote from the 1996 movie "Twister" (staring Helen Hunt & Bill Paxton) that says "We have cows" and a cow goes flying by. I think this is where many of my clients got the idea of asking for images of flying cows. A tornado is a violently rotating column of air that is in contact with both the surface of the earth and a cumulonimbus cloud. They are often referred to as twisters or cyclones. Tornadoes come in many shapes and sizes, but they are typically in the form of a visible condensation funnel, whose narrow end touches the earth and is often encircled by a cloud of debris and dust. This photo is available for licensing from @NatGeoCreative Photo by Mike Theiss @ExtremeNature

Cancelled but not forgotten ! This was one of the last KLM 747 jumbo jet airplanes to land at Princess Juliana International Airport (SXM) in Saint Maarten. KLM Airlines stopped buzzing tourists at Maho Beach with this enormous 747 jumbo jet airplane on October 28th, 2016. Tourists visit here from around the world to witness these planes fly right over this tropical destination. You can still experience this today, just not with a 747 jumbo jet. TAG a friend ! Photo by Mike Theiss @ExtremeNature

The almighty Mooney Falls standing 210 feet tall on Havasu Creek in the Havasupai Indian Reservation in Arizona. Havasu Creek is a tributary to the Colorado River, which it enters into the Grand Canyon. Mooney Falls is located over 2 miles from the village of Supai and only accessible via hiking the trail. TAG someone you want to hike to Mooney Falls with. #TeamCanon Photo by Mike Theiss @ExtremeNature

Connecting with the Northern Lights !! A truly memorable night shining man made energy back in the form of a blue laser into the Northern Lights in Iceland while surrounded by icebergs. The Aurora Borealis is a natural light display in the sky particularly in the high latitude regions, caused by the collision of energetic charged particles with atoms in the thermosphere. #teamcanon Photo copyright Mike Theiss @ExtremeNature TAG a friend you want to share an adventure with in 2017 !!

Tourists getting a close up view of the almighty Niagara Falls and its powerful force of rushing water. Niagara Falls, which sits on the border of the United States and Canada, is made up of three main waterfalls. This is a photo of Horseshoe Falls which is the most impressive of the three waterfalls and best seen from the Canadian side. Photo by Mike Theiss @ExtremeNature

Ingredients:
A bunch of wild garlic (leaves & flowers)
Â¾ cup of cashew (you can use pine nuts as well)
A generous handful of fresh basil leaves
1 cup of chopped watercress
2 tablespoons of olive oil
The juice of 1 lemon (use half if you donâ€™t like too lemony)
1 tablespoon of Love Raw Simple Greens
2 tablespoons of nutritional yeast
Salt & pepper to taste
Pasta of your choice (I have used brown rice spaghetti)
To sprinkle on top: fresh chives
.
Place the cashew in the food processor and blitz until you have a coarse mixture. Add all the other ingredients and blitz again for at least 1 minute until you have a creamy consistency. If you find the pesto too thick add a splash of water or more olive oil. 
Cook the pasta of your choice according to the cooking instructions. Mix about 2 tablespoon of pesto in each plate and sprinkle with the fresh chopped chives.  #vegancommunity #vegan #govegan #veganism #vegano

Terletak di pulau Honshu, Jepang, mempunyai tinggi Â 3776 meter dpl, Gunung FujiÂ (atau kadang disebut Fuji-san) adalah puncak tertinggi di dataran Jepang. Ketika musim dingin puncak gunung ini bersalju yang membuatnya semakin terlihat kokoh tapi tetap indah dipandang, gunung ini adalah simbol dari kota Tokyo. Gunung Fuji ini juga memiliki karakteristik sebagai gunung berapi. Meskipun letusan terakhirnya tercatat terakhir di tahun 1707, gunung ini masih dianggap sebagai gunung berapi aktif dan berisiko. Puri Ubud atau dikenal dengan nama Puri Saren Agung, yang merupakan sebuah istana sebagai pusat pemerintahan kerajaan yang berkuasa pada masanya. KeberadaanÂ Puri UbudÂ tertata dan terjaga dengan baik seperti bentuk aslinya, menjaga desain dan tata ruang tradisional Bali, serta ciri khas bangunan tradisional yang masih anda jumpai berdiri kokoh, dipenuhi ornamen ukiran Bali dengan kealamiannya. Rumah-rumah tradisional masih menghiasi pekarangan istana. Identitas Bali memang tampil begitu sempurna di Puri Ubud, sehingga mengingatkan pengunjung ke masa feodalisme. Tempat seperti ini memang sangat jarang bisa kita temui sekarang ini, dan Puri Saren Agung adalah salah stu objek wisata puri yang sangat populer di pulau Dewata.

I had to take a second on the roof to rest and to think. When my friend @maximilianbaier brought me to the #township to show me Lennys charity #communitykidspot the first time I didnâ€™t expect that this experience would touch and inspire me so much. Those people who support the kids in that shack in #Marikana own almost nothing themselves but still give them so much. That showed me very clearly how few it takes to give and support others in need. Especially when you are as privileged as me and most of the people I normally surround myself in the first world. If you have all the opportunities yourself, especially in my business you sometimes seem to forget the people who werenâ€™t that fortunate in life because youâ€™re all surrounded by healthyâ€‹, good looking and happy people. And it doesnâ€™t have to start with Townships in South Africa. Even if it had to take me there to get clear of that, you can start with people around you, people in the streets, friends, people you know who are in need. If you want to know more about Lennys #charity project you can find a link my bio. #bringsocialbacktomedia

girl power in the townships of Cape Town! 
I spent a few days at the charity project #communitykidspot in Marikana near #capetown where Lenny and those girls on my picture are taking care of destitute kids in the #township. They are living in comparably bad conditions themselves but they still spend all their time and almost all their own money to support the over 200 kids with one hot meal a day and provide them a place to get education and where they can develop their creativity. 
If you want to help me supporting Lenny and the girls with their project you can find a #fundraising link with more information on the project in my bio. #bringsocialbacktomedia #charity #crowdfunding #generosity

Muleshoe TX - A farmer has painted these 50 gallon drums to look like cows and heâ€™s pulling kids around the deserted Central Business District (CBD) of Muleshoe TX on Halloween. The kids are there for a â€œtrunk or treatâ€ where they drive to the CBD and open their trunks full of candy for the kids. In rural areas itâ€™s just too far to go from farm to farm for one piece of candy. @natgeo @natgeocreative @thephotosociety

There are six great aquifers in the world. In North America our great aquifer is the Ogallalaâ€”it stretches from South Dakota to the Texas panhandle. Twenty percent of our food and 40 percent of our beef rely on the aquifer. Itâ€™s unfortunate that weâ€™ve pumped the equivalent of two Lake Eries out, setting the stage for a new desert in the Texas panhandle and southern Kansas in the immediate future.

The aquifer recharges at different rates. Nebraska wins the water lottery; it is the only place you can see Ogallala water at the surface. The Ogallala takes a long time to recharge in Texas, where there are the most wells, the least regulation, the hottest temperatures (even before climate change), and the slowest recharge. Entire communities in this area are already running out of water.

Scarcity of water, fragile infrastructure, small dust bowls, the family farm crisis, Big Ag, and global urbanization leave some behind with few options. Small towns are disintegrating around their residents. There is rampant meth and opioid addiction in some of these places. If your hot water heater breaks, there isnâ€™t anyone in your entire county that can fix it.

I am from the Midwest, and the pain rural folks have gone through showed up this election. I saw this frustration first-hand working on the Ogallala aquifer story that ran in the August 2016 issue of National Geographic, but I never thought the level of frustration of these communities would manifest itself in this way. @natgeo @natgeocreative @thephotosociety

Wood River Nebraska - This was the last night of the last trip for an @natgeo assignment on the Ogallala Aquifer. I had bedded down in the blind when the cranes started to land for the night just outsideâ€¦ then the storm rolled in. Sand Hill Cranes are the grassland birds of the great plains. They migrate from Siberia to northern Mexico. They counted 413,000 Sandhill Cranes on this eveningâ€¦ more than theyâ€™ve ever counted before. These conservation groups are working like crazy to keep 20 miles of the Platte River braided and perfect habitat for the cranes that come through their area. @thephotosociety @natgeo @natgeocreative

Just across the state line from the Berdoza family are 88,000 agricultural wells tapping the Ogallala aquifer in the TX panhandle. The Berdoza family has been carrying water in 5 gallon buckets in the back of a pickup for FOUR YEARS. â€¦ they need to haul 105 gallons a day to meet their water needs and give their children bucket baths. @natgeo @natgeocreative @thephotosociety

Mennonite child on school bus piloted by Superintendent Joanna Martinez who wears many hats and is trying to figure out how to keep the school and community alive as they run out of water. She had 90 days of water left for 16 families. There are 88,000 wells around her in the TX panhandle and the area has the least water from the aquifer underneath, the least regulation, and the least recharge. @natgeo @natgeocreative @thephotosociety

Muleshoe TX - Central Business District (CBD) - Many of the businesses are for sale in the CBD or just boarded up. In general as the water runs out in the Ogallala aquifer, smaller towns in this area will dry up and disappear first. To be FAIRâ€¦ There is a strip of McDonaldâ€™s like businesses outside the CBDâ€¦ and the town does claim the smallest TV station run by a wonderful mother and son team. To see the video they did of me google Muleshoe Channel 6 and Randy Olson. @natgeo @natgeocreative @thephotosociety

Lazbuddie Texas the school superintendent also drives the school bus, and she is trying to figure out how to keep the school and community alive as they run out of water. At one point, she only had 90 days of water left for 16 families (teachers are housed at school complex). The well got down to 15 feet of standing water. Lazbuddie as well as towns all the way north to South Dakota depend on the Ogallala aquifer. There are 88,000 wells around her in the TX panhandle and the area has the least water from the aquifer underneath, the least regulation, the least recharge and the highest density of wells. On assignment @natgeo story. @natgeocreative @thephotosociety #schools #education #transportation #schoolbus

An American crocodile patrols the mangrove channels of Gardens of the Queen National Park Cuba. The crocodile rested on the seagrass covered bottom of the channel for minutes at a time and then rose slowly to take a breath of air and returned to the bottom to sleep again. Crocodiles are called the engineers of the mangroves because their movements create and maintain channels that enhance circulation of water and nutrients through the dense roots systems. Photographed on assignment for @natgeo Cubas Underwater Jewels in the Path of Tourism.  To view a video of working with this crocodile see @natgeo  With @natgeocreative @thephotosociety #ocean #cuba #crocodile #predator #extreme #followme for #moreocean @jenniferhayesig and @daviddoubilet

A moon jellyfish called Aurelia is the perfect home for a juvenile jack seeking protection from predators. I was working in the cool waters of Tasmania and swam into an aggregation of jellyfish. I looked long and hard for one or two that had resident jacks. Photographed on assignment for @natgeo with @thephotosociety @natgeocreative #ocean #bff #jellyfish #tasmania #australia #downunder #followme for #moreocean @daviddoubilet

A juvenile jack seeks protection within the soft tissues of a moon jellyfish (Aurelia) in the temperate waters of Waterfall Bay, Tasmania. Moon jellyfish are abundant in the sea and I find myself peering into them looking to see if they have a hitch hiker. Photographed on @natgeo assignment. With @natgeocreative @thephotosociety #ocean #jelkyfish #besuty #friends #jack #tasmania #australia for #moreocean #followme @daviddoubilet

BFF in a night sea. A small jack hitchhiker seeks the company and protection of a jellyfish in a night sea off Moalboal Philippines. We lowered a scaffolding of light into the sea at night to attract creatures from the depths three thousand feet below us. This jellyfish swam into the light with its hitchhiker and then disappeared back to the depths. Photographed on my current @natgeo assignment inside the Coral Triangle, The Philippines. #ocean #jellyfish #bff #philippines #coraltriangle #partners with @thephotosociety @natgeocreative follow @daviddoubilet and @jenniferhayesig

A very large and curious Maori wrasse followed our team around Sno Reef on the Great Barrier Reef. This big guy weighed several hundred pounds and had spear wounds from unsuccessful poaching encounters. The corals on the Great Barrier Reef are now in the midst of another unprecedented coral bleaching event. High sea temperatures in 2016 caused 90% of the 1200 mile long reef to bleach, a process where the tiny coral polyp loses its symbiotic algae due to heat stress. The algae provide valuable life sustaining nutrients to the coral and give it its color. If conditions improve quickly  enough some corals can recover from a bleach event while others die and become covered in algae. Scientist estimate that 20% + of the Great Barrier Reef corals did not recover during the 2016 event. The extent of the 2017 bleach is yet to be known. Sequential bleaching events weakens the corals resilience and speeds the death of the reef. For @natgeo @natgeocreative @thephotosociety #ocean #coralreef #coralbleaching #wrasse #greatbarrierreef #australia #worldheritagesite for #moreocean #followme @daviddoubilet

A trio of silky sharks patrol the surface of the sea at dusk in the open waters off Gardens of the Queen National Park, Cuba. Healthy coral reef and mangrove systems support intact food chains that in turn support robust populations of apex predators such sharks and crocodiles. This marine preserve is a time capsule in the Caribbean that looks much like it did when Columbus arrived here and named this place in honor of his patron Queen. Photo by @daviddoubilet for @natgeo with @natgeocreative @thephotosociety  #Ocean #Shark #Trio #Dance #Edge #Beauty #nationalpark  #Cuba #Gratitude  for #moreocean #followme @daviddoubilet

A Bayei fisherman standing in his mokoro peers into the water to watch me work in the dense  lily gardens of the Botswana's  Okavango Delta. The sunlight cast a long shadow behind the fisherman creating an effect that reminds me of an African tribal carving. The Okavango Delta, a tectonic trough that creates a seasonal wetland oasis in the heart of the Kalahari desert became the 1000th  UNESCO world heritage site in June 2014. The floodplains sustain life giving water to vast herds of African wildlife. Photographed on assignment for @natgeo Africas Miracle Delta. With @natgeocreative @thephotosociety @the_explorers_club #africa #botswana #edge #extreme #freshwater #okavangodelta #worldheritagesite #UNESCO for #moreocean follow @daviddoubilet

A hawksbill sea turtle hatchling paddles swiftly for the open sea at dusk in Gardens of the Queen National Park, Cuba. Hawksbill sea turtles are endangered. Encountering a hatchling in the wild is extremely rare because predation is high and survivors are few. I have only met a handful in my lifetime. These remarkable creatures are ancient mariners in the sea that battle over harvest, habitat loss, marine debris entrapment and now they face rising sea levels that threaten nesting beaches. To see more of Gardens of the Queen unique ecosystem see @natgeo recent story Caribbean Crown Jewels in November with @jenniferhayesig With @thephotosociety @the_explorers_club #ocean #turtle #baby  #cuba #nationalpark #endangeredspecies  #hatchling for #moreocean follow  @jenniferhayesig  @daviddoubilet

A curious leopard seal challenges his own reflection that he sees in the large 9 inch  glass dome of my underwater Seacam Housing near Danko Island Antarctica. A number of leopard seals were patrolling the shore near a large penguin colony waiting for a meal. These large seals are playful, curious and predatory.  We have to be cautious and vigilant while photographing them in the water on their terms. I am happy to have a large camera housing between them and myself for two reasons: 1 it attracts their curious nature and 2 the housing acts like a Roman Shield when they become TOO curious.
